# Project Architecture Rules

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This project follows a **Hybrid Architecture** (Firebase Hosting + Cloud Run).
> Detailed rules and deployment instructions are maintained in: [DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md](file:///Users/wayne/FiveNursings/RESOURCES/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md#L105-L131)

## Core Deployment
- **Backend (API)**: `gcloud run deploy api --source . --project fivenursings-73917017-a0dfd`
- **Frontend**: `firebase deploy --only hosting`

## Backend Modularity (V2.0)
- **THIN ENTRY POINT**: KEEP `server/index.js` under 80 lines. Do NOT add business logic there.
- **ROUTE ISOLATION**: ALWAYS create a new file in `/server/routes/` for new features.
- **PRECEDENCE**: ALWAYS mount custom routes BEFORE calling `routeGenerator` or generic routes in `index.js`.
- **DRY CRUD**: Use `server/utils/routeGenerator.js` for boilerplate CRUD endpoints.
- **USER ID STANDARD**: ALWAYS use `resolveUserIds` or `resolvePrimaryId` from `server/utils/idResolver.js` for all user-related queries.
- **FORMATTING**: ALWAYS use `format()` from `server/utils/index.js` to normalize MongoDB documents before sending to frontend.
- **DB ACCESS**: Use `server/db.js` for connection logic. Export models from `server/models/index.js`.
